    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense from a purely income-based perspective. But when you say Riverview and Eastside are \"high risk,\" aren't you assuming that the racial makeup contributes to that risk somehow? Like, if a neighborhood has a high concentration of minority residents, does that change the risk profile beyond just the median income numbers you're looking at?",
