      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While median income is a key indicator, the racial and ethnic makeup can signal differing socio-economic dynamics and community stability factors. High concentrations of minority residents, especially when paired with lower incomes, can sometimes correlate with areas facing higher rates of systemic economic challenges or investment hurdles. However, it is crucial to avoid making direct causal links; broader factors like employment rates, crime statistics, and historical disinvestment are far stronger predictors of true real estate risk.",
